    </admin_routes>
  </route_discovery>

  <element_checks>
    For each element type, perform these checks:

    <links>
      - Click each link
      - Verify navigation occurs OR expected behavior (anchor, external)
      - Check for 404s, broken routes
      - Check external links open correctly
    </links>

    <buttons>
      - Click each button
      - Verify expected action occurs
      - Check loading states appear/disappear
      - Check disabled states respected
      - Check form submission buttons trigger validation
    </buttons>

    <dropdowns_selects>
      - Open dropdown/select
      - Verify options are visible
      - Select each option (or sample if many)
      - Verify selection is reflected in UI
      - Check multi-select behavior if applicable
    </dropdowns_selects>

    <forms>
      - Submit empty form (check validation)
      - Submit with invalid data (check error messages)
      - Submit with valid data (check success state)
      - Check field-level validation feedback
      - Check required field indicators
    </forms>

    <modals_dialogs>
      - Open modal via trigger
      - Verify content loads
      - Check close button works
      - Check backdrop click closes (if expected)
      - Check escape key closes (if expected)
      - Check form submissions within modal
    </modals_dialogs>

    <tabs_accordions>
      - Click each tab/accordion header
      - Verify content switches/reveals
      - Check active state styling
      - Check content is not empty
    </tabs_accordions>

    <navigation>
      - Test main nav links
      - Test sidebar navigation
      - Test breadcrumbs
      - Test back/forward browser navigation
      - Test mobile menu toggle (if responsive)
    </navigation>
  </element_checks>

  <expected_outputs>
    - Single file: _PLAN.md (overwritten with UX audit results)
    - YAML frontmatter with audit metadata
    - Summary with element counts and failure rates
    - Route-by-route breakdown of tested elements
    - Issue blocks with:
      - Severity (Critical/Major/Minor)
      - Element type and selector
      - Screenshot filename
      - Steps to reproduce
      - Expected behavior
      - Actual behavior
      - Proposed remedy
    - Prioritized remediation plan
  </expected_outputs>

  <severity_rules>
    - Critical: Element completely broken, blocks user flow, crashes page, data loss risk
    - Major: Element partially broken, confusing behavior, significant UX degradation
    - Minor: Visual glitch, inconsistent styling, accessibility improvement needed
  </severity_rules>

  <evidence_rule>
    NO ISSUE MAY BE REPORTED WITHOUT:
    - Screenshot filename showing the element/issue
    - Element identifier (selector, aria-label, or text content)
    - Console errors (if any)
    - Network failures (if any)
    - Exact steps to reproduce
  </evidence_rule>

  <recovery_policy>
    If page crashes or element interaction fails:
    1. Capture screenshot and console state immediately
    2. Record the failure with full evidence
    3. Navigate back to a stable page
    4. Continue with remaining elements/routes
    5. Do NOT stop the entire audit for single failures
  </recovery_policy>

  <performance_limits>
    - Max 5 seconds wait per element interaction
    - Max 30 seconds per page load
    - Max 3 retry attempts per element before marking as failure
    - Skip infinite scrolling content after 10 items
  </performance_limits>

  <activation_conditions>
    - After frontend UI changes
    - Before releases (acceptance testing)
    - After component library updates
    - After accessibility audits
    - On-demand quality checks
  </activation_conditions>
</audit_manifest>
